 Prompt 4 – First Response Email

## Version 1 (v4.1)

### Prompt
Write a reply to a customer enquiry.

Respond 

Hi [Customer Name],

Thanks for reaching out—great to hear from you!

We’d love to help you find the right solution for your café. Flexikitch makes it easy to access high-quality kitchen equipment without the stress of large upfront costs, while giving you flexibility as your business grows.

To recommend the best option, could you share a bit more about your café (e.g., size, equipment needed, or any current challenges)?

Once we have that, we can put together a tailored plan for you.

Looking forward to helping your café thrive!
[Your Name]


### Change Made
Initial version

### Observed Effect
Basic reply with no personalisation or CTA 
Weak engagement
Not aligned with sales goals

### Lesson Learned
Responses must include structure and purpose


## Version 2 (v4.2)

### Prompt
Imagine yourself as a Flexikitch sales representative. Write a first response email to a café owner enquiry. Include thank you, relevant benefits, and CTA to book consultation. Keep professional and under 150 words.

Respond 

Hi [Customer Name],

Thank you for reaching out to Flexikitch—we appreciate your interest.

We help café owners access high-quality kitchen equipment without large upfront costs through our flexible rent-to-own model. This means better cash flow, the ability to upgrade as your business grows, and ongoing maintenance support to keep everything running smoothly.

We’d love to understand your café’s needs and recommend the best solution tailored to you.

Please feel free to book a quick consultation at your convenience here: [Insert Link]

Looking forward to supporting your café’s success.

Best regards,
[Your Name]
Flexikitch Team


### Change Made
Added sales representative role, defined structure (thank you, benefits, CTA), added constraints like tone and word limit

### Observed Effect
Consistent, professional responses and higher engagement potential

### Lesson Learned
Structured prompts improve focus on conversion communication
